&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;Nice, all tests passed!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;summary&quot;&gt;Summary&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this third post, I took on the not entirely trivial task of computing all valid moves for a piece in its starting position.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I avoided implementing it as a recursive algorithm, since that would limit how large our boards can get.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We reminded ourselves that code should live where we expect to find it.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We also took the opportunity to make the code easier to work with, by specifying pieces in a more readable way, and with that change we could easily support three different Tetris variants.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hope you had just as much fun as I did üòÉ&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Happy Coding!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
